Differentiating term-by-term and using the chain rule, we
obtain:\begin{align*}
y'(x) &= (e^{\sin x}+x)'
\\ &= e^{\sin x} \cdot (\sin x)' + 1
\\ &= e^{\sin x} \cos x + 1
\\
\\ y'(0) &= e^{\sin(0)} \cos(0) + 1
\\ &= e^{0} \cdot 1 + 1
\\ &= 2
\end{align*}

The equation of the tangent line is therefore:\begin{align*}
y &= 2(x-0)+1
\\ &= {\color{blue}2x+1}
\end{align*}
